text.0:
A tweet with a photo of heavy traffic claiming that it was shot on Kenya's Thika Road on November 17 is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The photo is actually of a queue for food in the US: https://t.co/4SnUe0VfPU
text.1:
A Facebook post with a photo of guns on the ground claiming they were handed over by forces aligned to Tigray’s regional government is :cross_mark: FALSE

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The guns were not captured from forces in the Tigray region: https://t.co/pZHPZxUaVs
text.2:
A Facebook post with a photo showing a person praying in the middle of a road and surrounded by lions is ALTERED.

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: The original image is of a dozen lions lying on a road in Kruger National Park, South Africa, and does not include the praying man: https://t.co/I8ncy9cIdv
text.3:
A tweet with an image claiming to show supporters of the National Unity Platform (NUP) in Uganda destroying a road is :cross_mark: FALSE.

:camera_with_flash: The image is from South Africa, and was shot in September: https://t.co/GpPYndG08b
